# CustomView — list filters

ListView filter dropdown ("Wszystkie", "Moje", ...). Per-module rows in `vtiger_customview` (`entitytype` = module name, `cvid`, `viewname`, `userid`, `status`).

## Where the code lives

| Concern | File |
|---|---|
| Save action (create/edit/duplicate) | `src/Modules/CustomView/Actions/Save.php` |
| Record model (save, grouping, sort) | `src/Modules/CustomView/Models/Record.php` |
| Edit form view (AJAX, builds EditView) | `src/Modules/CustomView/Views/EditAjax.php` |
| Edit form template | `layouts/basic/modules/CustomView/EditView.tpl` |
| Filter editor JS | `public/layouts/basic/modules/CustomView/resources/CustomView.js` (+ `.min.js`) |
| Dropdown / featured render | `layouts/basic/modules/Base/ListViewHeader.tpl` |
| Filter create/edit/duplicate/delete click events | `public/layouts/basic/modules/Base/resources/ListView.js` (`registerEditFilterClickEvent` etc.) |

- Save flow: `CustomView.js` submit → `saveFilter()` posts the `#CustomView` form (`action=Save`) → `Save.php`. The hidden `#record` carries `cvid` (empty = create, set = edit). Duplicate uses `&duplicate=1` on EditAjax → `RECORD_ID` blanked so it saves as new.

## Status constants (`src/View/CustomView.php`)

`CV_STATUS_DEFAULT=0`, `CV_STATUS_PRIVATE=1`, `CV_STATUS_PENDING=2`, `CV_STATUS_PUBLIC=3`, `CV_STATUS_SYSTEM=4`. The built-in "All" filter has `viewname='All'`, `status=0`.

## Behaviors (intentional, do not "restore")

- **Duplicate filter names are allowed.** There is no `checkDuplicate()` / `LBL_CUSTOM_VIEW_NAME_DUPLICATES_EXIST` — that blocking was removed on purpose. `Save.php` just saves.
- **Dropdown grouping is per owner** (`Record::getAllByGroup()`): group order = Systemowe (built-in "All" + `status=SYSTEM`), then Moje (current user), then one group per other owner (label = `getOwnerName()`, sorted). Group keys are the already-translated labels.
- Templates iterate `$CUSTOM_VIEWS` as `key=GROUP_LABEL` and render `<optgroup label='{$GROUP_LABEL}'>` directly — **no** `LBL_CV_GROUP_*` prefix building, no `[ owner ]` suffix on option text. Same pattern in `Calendar.tpl`, `Campaigns/RelatedList.tpl`, dashboards `ChartFilter.tpl`/`MiniListWizard.tpl`.

## Gotchas

- `getAllByGroup()` consumers: ListView, Calendar dashboard, Campaigns RelatedList, ChartFilter, MiniListWizard, TreeRecords — update all if you change the structure.
- After editing `EditView.tpl` or any `.tpl`, wipe `cache/templates_c/*.php`.
- Per-filter default sort lives in `vtiger_customview.sort` as `{column},{ASC|DESC}` — see `Record::parseSortValue()` / `formatSortValue()`.

## Advanced filter conditions

UI: `layouts/basic/modules/Base/AdvanceFilter.tpl` + `AdvanceFilterCondition.tpl`, JS `AdvanceFilter.js`. Operators keyed by **`Field::getFieldType()`** (single letter `V`, `N`, …) via `ADVANCED_FILTER_OPTIONS_BY_TYPE` — **not** by semantic type (`modulesMultipicklist`).

- **`typeofdata` with `~` suffix** (e.g. `V~O`): `getFieldType()` must strip after `transformFieldTypeOfData()` — otherwise operator lookup fails (`V~O` ≠ `V`) and comparator shows only **Brak**. `getCustomViewColumnName()` must use `getFieldType()` so saved `columnname` suffix matches option values.
- **Semantic types** (`modules`, `modulesMultipicklist`): `Field::getCustomViewAdvancedFilterOps()` → `e`, `n`, `y`, `ny` (same labels as picklist: **jest równe** / **nie jest równe**). JS `AdvanceFilter.js` filters out string ops (`s`, `ew`, `c`, `k`) for these types. **QueryField:** `modulesMultipicklist` comparator **`e`** → `ModulesMultipicklistField::operatorE()` delegates to `operatorC` (module membership in ` |##| ` storage) — see `uitypes.mdc`.
- **Save:** multipicklist / modules fields submit `name[]` → value is **array** in `advfilterlist`. `Record::setConditionsForFilter()` must `implode(',', …)` before any `explode(',', $value)`.
- **Owner / assignee (`om`):** UI label „Aktualnie zalogowany użytkownik” → comparator code **`om`**, empty `value`. Do not save as `e` with NULL — check `advfilterlist` in POST / `vtiger_cvadvfilter.comparator`. JS: sync `comparatorValue` hidden field; skip rows with comparator `none` in `getValues()`.
- **AdvanceFilter.js load order:** define `AdvanceFilter_Multipicklist_Field_Js` before `AdvanceFilter_Modulesmultipicklist_Field_Js` / `AdvanceFilter_Taxes_Field_Js`.
- **Renamed field migrations:** update `vtiger_cvcolumnlist`, **`vtiger_cvadvfilter`**, and **`vtiger_cvstdfilter`** (not column list alone). Example: EmailTemplates `module_name` → `modules` (`m260703_000002` / `000003`).
